#' Adds documentation of a dataset to a datapackage

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Add information about variables in a dataset to a \code{datapackage.json} metadata file.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param path A character vector of paths to plain-text tabular data files.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param meta Information about each data file. A list with a list entry for each entry in \code{path}; see details.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param package_path Package to add the metadata to; path to the .json file, or a list with the read-in version.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dir Directory in which to look for \code{path}, and write \code{package_path}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param write Logical; if \code{FALSE}, returns the \code{paths} metadata without reading or rewriting

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' \code{package_path}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' @param refresh Logical; if \code{TRUE}, will remove any existing dataset information.

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' @param sha A number specifying the Secure Hash Algorithm function,

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' if \code{openssl} is available (checked with \code{Sys.which('openssl')}).

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param clean Logical; if \code{TRUE}, strips special characters before saving.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param open_after Logical; if \code{TRUE}, opens the written datapackage after saving.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' \code{meta} should be a list with unnamed entries for entry in \code{path}, and each entry can include a named entry

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' for any of these:

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' \describe{

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{source}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'   A list or list of lists with entries for at least \code{name}, and ideally for \code{url}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{ids}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#'   A list or list of lists with entries for at least \code{variable} (the name of a variable in the dataset).

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#'   Might also include \code{map} with a list or path to a JSON file resulting in a list with an

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'   entry for each ID, and additional information about that entity, to be read in a its features.

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'   All files will be loaded to help with aggregation, but local files will be included in the datapackage,

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'   whereas hosted files will be loaded client-side.

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{time}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'   A string giving the name of a variable in the dataset representing a repeated observation of the same entity.

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{variables}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'   A list with named entries providing more information about the variables in the dataset.

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#' \dontrun{

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#' # write example data

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#' write.csv(mtcars, "mtcars.csv")

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    42

#' Add dynamic text to a website

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Adds a textual output based on the current state of input elements.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param text A vector of text to be parsed; see details.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param tag Tag name of the element containing the text.

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id Unique ID of the output element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' @param class Class names to add to the output's element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' @param condition A conditional statement to decide visibility of the entire output element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' @details

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' \describe{

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{Input References}{\code{text} can include references to inputs by ID within curly brackets

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#'     (e.g., \code{"{input_id}").}}

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{Conditions}{Multiple entries in \code{text} translate to separate elements. Each entry can be

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#'     conditioned on a statement within curly brackets following an initial question mark

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#'     (e.g., \code{"?{input_a != 1}Input A is not 1"}). If no statement is included after the question mark,

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#'     the entry will be conditioned on a referred to input (\code{TRUE} if anything is selected).}

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{Buttons}{Embedded reset buttons can be specified within square brackets (e.g., \code{"Reset[r input_id]"}).

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#'     Text before the brackets will be the button's display text, with multiple words included within parentheses

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#'     (e.g., \code{"(Reset Input A)[r input_a]"}). If the text is a reference, this will be the default reset

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#'     reference (e.g., \code{"{input_a}[r]"} is the same as \code{"{input_a}[r input_a]"}).}

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' }

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' @examples

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' # text that shows the current value of `input_a`, and resets it on click

#' output_text("Selection: {input_a}[r]")

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'

#' # adds a parenthetical if the value of the input is 0

                    32
                    
                    
                      
output_text <- function(text, tag = "p", id = NULL, class = NULL, condition = NULL) {

                    4x
                    
                      
  caller <- parent.frame()

#' Add a button to a website

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' Adds a button to reset an input or trigger a predefined function (including data export) to a website.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' @param label Text in the button for the user.

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' @param target The ID of an input element to reset, a vector with IDs of input elements as names and values to set

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' those inputs to as values, or the name of a function to trigger (e.g., \code{c(input_a = 1)}). Available function

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' are \code{refresh} (to force a reprocessing of the current input state), \code{reset_selection} (to reset all input

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' elements that are not settings), \code{reset_storage} (to clear local storage, reset all settings, and reload),

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' \code{export} (to download data), \code{copy} (to save an API link to the clipboard), and

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' \code{filter} (to open a data filter menu).

                    		
                  

                  

                    12
                    
                    
                      
#' This can also be a URL (including protocol) for a button-like link.

                    		
                  

                  

                    13
                    
                    
                      
#' @param id Unique ID of the element to be created.

                    		
                  

                  

                    14
                    
                    
                      
#' @param dataview Name of a data view to get selection and filter options from for export.

                    		
                  

                  

                    15
                    
                    
                      
#' @param query A list of query parameters, if \code{target} is \code{"export"} or \code{"copy"}. See the API section.

                    		
                  

                  

                    16
                    
                    
                      
#' @param from_api Logical; if \code{TRUE}, \code{target} is \code{"export"}, and an endpoint has been provided

                    		
                  

                  

                    17
                    
                    
                      
#' in \code{\link{site_build}}, links to the API rather than exporting from the browser.

                    		
                  

                  

                    18
                    
                    
                      
#' @param class Additional class names to add to the element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    19
                    
                    
                      
#' @param ... Additional attributes to set on the element.

                    		
                  

                  

                    20
                    
                    
                      
#' @param note Text to display as a tooltip for the button.

                    		
                  

                  

                    21
                    
                    
                      
#' @seealso For buttons to select between a set of options, use \code{\link{input_buttongroup}}.

                    		
                  

                  

                    22
                    
                    
                      
#' @section API Query:

                    		
                  

                  

                    23
                    
                    
                      
#' The \code{query} argument can be used to specify export options for a download button.

                    		
                  

                  

                    24
                    
                    
                      
#' These options can also be included as query parameters in a site API's URL:

                    		
                  

                  

                    25
                    
                    
                      
#' \describe{

                    		
                  

                  

                    26
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{Format}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    27
                    
                    
                      
#'     These options affect the format of the returned file:

                    		
                  

                  

                    28
                    
                    
                      
#'     \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    29
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{file_format}}: Specifies the separator between columns:

                    		
                  

                  

                    30
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{'csv'} (default) for commas, or \code{'tsv'} for tabs.

                    		
                  

                  

                    31
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{table_format}}: Specifies the layout of the data:

                    		
                  

                  

                    32
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{'tall'} for a row for each value, with all values in the same column

                    		
                  

                  

                    33
                    
                    
                      
#'       (repeats over entities, times, and variables);

                    		
                  

                  

                    34
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{'mixed'} (default) for a row for each time, with a column for each variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    35
                    
                    
                      
#'       (repeats over entities);

                    		
                  

                  

                    36
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{'wide'} for a row for each entity, with a column for each variable at each time.

                    		
                  

                  

                    37
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{features}}: Specifies which features to include in the

                    		
                  

                  

                    38
                    
                    
                      
#'       first columns of the file: A list with names for year column name, and value with the

                    		
                  

                  

                    39
                    
                    
                      
#'       feature name to include in that column. Currently not available through the URL.

                    		
                  

                  

                    40
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{include}}: Specifies which variables to include:

                    		
                  

                  

                    41
                    
                    
                      
#'       a vector or variable names, or (for the URL interface) a string with variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    42
                    
                    
                      
#'       names separated by commas. By default, all variables are included.

                    		
                  

                  

                    43
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{exclude}}: Specifies which variables to exclude:

                    		
                  

                  

                    44
                    
                    
                      
#'       a vector or variable names, or (for the URL interface) a string with variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    45
                    
                    
                      
#'       names separated by commas.

                    		
                  

                  

                    46
                    
                    
                      
#'     }

                    		
                  

                  

                    47
                    
                    
                      
#'   }

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      
#'   \item{Filters}{

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    
                    
                      
#'     These options can be used to subset data:

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    
                    
                      
#'     \itemize{

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{dataset}}: The name of a dataset, or vector (comma separated string)

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
#'       of dataset names. Includes all datasets by default.

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{variable[component]=value}}: Sets conditions

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    
                    
                      
#'       on the summary of a variable. The summary of a variable is within each entity, which results in

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    
                    
                      
#'       a set of summary components: \code{"first"}, \code{"min"}, \code{"mean"}, \code{"sum"},

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{"max"}, \code{"last"}. The \code{=} sign can be another operator:

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{"!="}, \code{">="}, \code{"<="}. values can be comma-separated sets of values.

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{feature=value}}: Sets conditions on a feature of each entity.

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    
                    
                      
#'       \item \strong{\code{time_range}}: Selects a time or time range to include:

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    
                    
                      
#'       \code{">="} or \code{"<="} with a single minimal or maximal time, or \code{"="}

#'     }

#'   }

#' }
